m gateway.platforms.feishu_comment import _reverse_lookup_wiki_token\n\n        mock_exec.return_value = (500, \"internal error\", {})\n        result = self._run(_reverse_lookup_wiki_token(Mock(), \"docx\", \"docx_abc\"))\n        self.assertIsNone(result)\n\n    @patch(\"gateway.platforms.feishu_comment._reverse_lookup_wiki_token\", new_callable=AsyncMock)\n    @patch(\"gateway.platforms.feishu_comment_rules.has_wiki_keys\", return_value=True)\n    @patch(\"gateway.platforms.feishu_comment_rules.is_user_allowed\", return_value=True)\n    @patch(\"gateway.platforms.feishu_comment_rules.resolve_rule\")\n   \n\n--- skills/software-development/token-saving-workflow/SKILL.md (lines 1-100) [markdown] score: 0.5000 ---\n---\nname: token-saving-workflow\ndescription: Workflow ประหยัด Token + ป้องกัน Loop — SocratiCode Boundary, No-Guess Policy, Code Precision, Sequential Plan, Search Hierarchy, Zapier\n---\n\n# Token Saving Workflow\n\n## Purpose\nรวบรวมกฎการใช้เครื่องมือและ Workflow สำหรับประหยัด Token และป้องกันวนลูป\n\n## Rules\n\n### Token Firewall v2.0 (Emergency Token Conservation)\nTriggered when user explicitly requests \"ประหยัดฉุกเฉิน\" or \"Token Firewall\".\n\n| Rule | Threshold | Action |\n|---|---|---|\n| Hard Token Limit | keepRecentTokens=8000, reserveTokens=4000 | Drop history beyond this; never backfill |\n| Auto-Summary Reset | Every 10 sentences | Summarize task state in 3-line English, then reset context to that summary only |\n| External Storage | File >2000 tokens | Offload to disk first; read back only the chunk the user asks about |\n| Kill-Switch | >200,000 tokens/hour | Hard stop immediately; notify Telegram |\n| Anti-Loop | >3 repetitive rounds | Stop execution; write debug_logic.txt; do not continue |\n\n**Pitfall 1:** A hand-written JSON config file on disk does NOT integrate automatically. Hermes Gateway does not read arbitrary JSON files for token limits. These rules are enforced purely via agent behavior and memory, not via external configuration.\n\n**Pitfall 2 — MEMORY CRISIS:** Persistent memory capacity is only ~2,200 chars and fills fast. At 91%+ usage, auto-purge kills oldest entries. Proactively backup memory to disk BEFORE purging. Compress multiple related rules into single concise entries to prevent critical data loss. See `references/memory-management.md`.\n\n### Auto-Organize Protocol v2.0 (Automatic Focus & Cleanup)\nTriggered when user requests \"จัดระเบียบและโฟกัสอัตโนมัติ\".\n\n| Module | Behavior |\n|---|---|\n| Active Garbage Collection | After each completed task → emit a 3-line English state summary → instruct self to drop all micro-details of that task immediately |\n| 5-Turn Compression | Every 5 messages → auto-compress memory to: (a) pending tasks only, (b) key pat\n\n--- skills/autonomous-ai-agents/codex/SKILL.md (lines 91-130) [markdown] score: 0.4500 ---\n\n# Launch Codex in each\nterminal(command=\"codex --yolo exec 'Fix issue #78: <description>. Commit when done.'\", workdir=\"/tmp/issue-78\", background=true, pty=true)\nterminal(command=\"codex --yolo exec 'Fix issue #99: <description>. Commit when done.'\", workdir=\"/tmp/issue-99\", background=true, pty=true)\n\n# Monitor\nprocess(action=\"list\")\n\n# After completion, push and create PRs\nterminal(command=\"cd /tmp/issue-78 && git push -u origin fix/issue-78\")\nterminal(command=\"gh pr create --repo user/repo --head fix/issue-78 --title 'fix: ...' --body '...'\")\n\n# Cleanup\nterminal(command=\"git worktree remove /tmp/issue-78\", workdir=\"~/project\")\n```\n\n## Batch PR Reviews\n\n```\n# Fetch all PR refs\nterminal(command=\"git fetch origin '+refs/pull/*/head:refs/remotes/origin/pr/*'\", workdir=\"~/project\")\n\n# Review multiple PRs in parallel\nterminal(command=\"codex exec 'Review PR #86. git diff origin/main...origin/pr/86'\", workdir=\"~/project\", background=true, pty=true)\nterminal(command=\"codex exec 'Review PR #87. git diff origin/main...origin/pr/87'\", workdir=\"~/project\", background=true, pty=t